        <h2>Aerial measurement tools for roofing</h2>
        <p>Aerial measurement is a category of its own, separate from project management software. The leading platforms:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>EagleView:</strong> Industry standard. Generates precise slope measurements, pitch, and area calculations from aerial imagery. Integrates with JobNimbus, AccuLynx, and others. $40–$120 per report depending on detail level.</li>
          <li><strong>Hover:</strong> Uses homeowner or contractor photos to build a 3D model with measurements. More cost-effective than EagleView for many residential jobs.</li>
          <li><strong>RoofSnap:</strong> Mobile measurement tool that works from photos and satellite imagery. Good for contractors who need fast estimates in the field.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What roofing software won't fix</h2>
        <p>No software fixes poor estimating accuracy, inadequate crew training, or weak material management. Software helps you organize and execute what you already do well — it doesn't replace operational discipline. Start with the systems you need most, get your team using them, then add features as you grow.</p>

